---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { socials } from '../../data/socials';
---

<PageLayout 
  title="Panel Facilitation" 
  description="Expert panel facilitation using the Joseph Campbell Hero's Journey framework to create memorable, engaging experiences for audiences and panelists alike."
>
  <article class="facilitation-page">
    <header class="page-header">
      <span class="kicker">Speaking Services</span>
      <h1>Panel Facilitation</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        I facilitate panels that audiences remember and panelists enjoy—using 
        the <strong>Joseph Campbell Hero's Journey</strong> as a framework for 
        creating narrative-driven, engaging conversations.
      </p>
    </header>
    
    <section class="approach-section">
      <div class="approach-intro">
        <h2>The Hero's Journey Approach</h2>
        <p>
          Most panels are forgettable. A moderator reads questions, panelists give rehearsed answers, 
          and the audience checks their phones. That's not facilitation—that's reading a script.
        </p>
        <p>
          I approach panel facilitation differently. By applying Joseph Campbell's monomyth—the 
          Hero's Journey—I structure conversations that have <strong>narrative arc</strong>, 
          <strong>emotional resonance</strong>, and <strong>genuine discovery</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="journey-framework">
        <h3>The Framework in Practice</h3>
        
        <div class="journey-stages">
          <div class="stage">
            <span class="stage-number">I</span>
            <h4>The Ordinary World</h4>
            <p>
              We begin with context. What was the world like before? What problem existed? 
              This grounds the audience and establishes stakes.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="stage">
            <span class="stage-number">II</span>
            <h4>The Call to Adventure</h4>
            <p>
              What moment or realization launched the journey? These are the stories 
              that make panelists human and relatable.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="stage">
            <span class="stage-number">III</span>
            <h4>Trials & Transformation</h4>
            <p>
              The meat of the conversation. What obstacles appeared? What was learned? 
              This is where real insight emerges.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="stage">
            <span class="stage-number">IV</span>
            <h4>The Return</h4>
            <p>
              What wisdom do the heroes bring back? What can the audience take with them? 
              We end with actionable insight.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <section class="why-section">
      <h2>Why This Works</h2>
      
      <div class="benefits-grid">
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>For Audiences</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Stories are memorable; bullet points are not</li>
            <li>Narrative arc creates engagement and anticipation</li>
            <li>Emotional connection drives retention</li>
            <li>Real insight, not rehearsed talking points</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>For Panelists</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Questions that invite storytelling, not recitation</li>
            <li>Space to be human, not just an expert</li>
            <li>Genuine conversation, not performance</li>
            <li>An experience they'll want to repeat</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>For Organizers</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Memorable content people talk about after</li>
            <li>Differentiated from typical conference panels</li>
            <li>Panelists who become advocates</li>
            <li>Content that works for recordings</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <section class="expertise-section">
      <h2>Areas of Expertise (and Beyond)</h2>
      
      <div class="expertise-grid">
        <div class="expertise-block">
          <h3>Deep Expertise</h3>
          <p>
            I can go deep on panels covering:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>APIs, developer experience, and platform strategy</li>
            <li>AI transformation and enterprise adoption</li>
            <li>Enterprise modernization and architecture</li>
            <li>Technology leadership and career development</li>
            <li>Contact centers and customer experience</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="expertise-block expertise-block--alt">
          <h3>Curious Outsider</h3>
          <p>
            Some of my best facilitation happens in domains where I'm <em>not</em> the expert.
          </p>
          <p>
            When I don't know a field deeply, I ask the questions the audience is thinking. 
            I'm not trying to show off my knowledge—I'm genuinely curious. This creates 
            space for panelists to explain, for jargon to be unpacked, and for real 
            understanding to emerge.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Expertise isn't always an asset in facilitation—curiosity is.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <section class="process-section">
      <h2>The Process</h2>
      
      <ol class="process-steps">
        <li>
          <strong>Discovery Call</strong>
          <p>Understand the event, audience, and desired outcomes</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Panelist Pre-Interviews</strong>
          <p>30-minute calls to find the stories worth telling</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Narrative Design</strong>
          <p>Craft the arc: where we start, where we're going, how we get there</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Facilitation</strong>
          <p>Guide the conversation live, adapting to what emerges</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Follow-up</strong>
          <p>Debrief with organizers, optional content for continued engagement</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>
    
    <section class="cta-section">
      <div class="cta-content">
        <h2>Let's Create Something Memorable</h2>
        <p>
          Whether you have a topic I know deeply or something entirely new to me, 
          I'd love to discuss how we can make your panel unforgettable.
        </p>
        <div class="cluster" style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">
          <a href={`mailto:${socials.email}?subject=Panel%20Facilitation%20Inquiry`} class="btn btn--primary">
            Discuss Your Panel
          </a>
          <a href="/speaking/" class="btn">
            ← Back to Speaking
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .facilitation-page {
    max-width: 48rem;
  }
  
  .facilitation-page section {
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    padding-top: var(--space-8);
    border-top: var(--border-thin);
  }
  
  .facilitation-page section:first-of-type {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    padding-top: 0;
    border-top: 0;
  }
  
  .approach-intro {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }
  
  .approach-intro h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  
  /* Journey Framework */
  .journey-framework h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  
  .journey-stages {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }
  
  @media (min-width: 48rem) {
    .journey-stages {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }
  
  .stage {
    padding: var(--space-4);
    background: var(--color-paper-dark);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
  }
  
  .stage-number {
    font-family: var(--font-headline);
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-rule);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  
  .stage h4 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
  }
  
  .stage p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--color-ink-light);
    margin: 0;
  }
  
  /* Benefits */
  .benefits-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }
  
  @media (min-width: 48rem) {
    .benefits-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }
  
  .benefit {
    border-top: 2px solid var(--color-ink);
    padding-top: var(--space-4);
  }
  
  .benefit h3 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  
  .benefit ul {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--color-ink-light);
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
    margin: 0;
  }
  
  .benefit li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
  }
  
  /* Expertise */
  .expertise-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }
  
  @media (min-width: 48rem) {
    .expertise-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }
  
  .expertise-block {
    padding: var(--space-5);
    background: var(--color-paper-dark);
  }
  
  .expertise-block h3 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  
  .expertise-block p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  }
  
  .expertise-block ul {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
  }
  
  .expertise-block--alt {
    background: transparent;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
  }
  
  /* Process */
  .process-steps {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    counter-reset: step;
  }
  
  .process-steps li {
    position: relative;
    padding: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-4) var(--space-12);
    border-bottom: var(--border-thin);
    counter-increment: step;
  }
  
  .process-steps li::before {
    content: counter(step);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: var(--space-4);
    font-family: var(--font-headline);
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    width: var(--space-8);
  }
  
  .process-steps li strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
  }
  
  .process-steps li p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--color-ink-light);
    margin: 0;
  }
  
  /* CTA */
  .cta-section {
    background: var(--color-paper-dark);
    padding: var(--space-8);
    margin-left: calc(-1 * var(--gutter));
    margin-right: calc(-1 * var(--gutter));
    border-top: var(--border-accent);
  }
  
  @media (min-width: 48rem) {
    .cta-section {
      margin-left: 0;
      margin-right: 0;
    }
  }
  
  .cta-content h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  
  .cta-content p {
    max-width: 50ch;
  }
</style>
